725052f-b.text:
19th Avenue, north side, between 45th and 47th Streets, showing the Cassabeer House (white) and barns, the view being north from the avenue toward the East River. Views 2 and 3 show closer views of the house, seen from 45th Street near the river shore. In 1933 the house was known as Steinway Lodge.
P. L. Sperr  June 3, 1927
NO REPRODUCTIONS  Views 1,2,3

725053f-c.text:
19th Avenue, north side, between 45th and 47th Streets, showing, in the distance, the white Cassabeer House, known in 1933 as Steinway Lodge. A large shingled barn can be seen on the right. The views are north from 19th Avenue, toward
the East River, which the house overlooks.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  Views 1,2: 1923
MAY BE REPRODUCED  View 3: 1925
